      <constitutionalAuthorityStatementText>&lt;pre&gt;[Congressional Record Volume 169, Number 33 (Friday, February 17, 2023)][House]From the Congressional Record Online through the Government Publishing Office [&lt;a href="https://www.gpo.gov"&gt;www.gpo.gov&lt;/a&gt;]By Mr. CARTER of Georgia:H.R. 1070Congress has the power to enact this legislation pursuantto the following:Clause 3 of Section 8 of article I of the U.S. Constitutionprovides Congress with the power to regulate commerce.The single subject of this legislation is:To increase American energy production and restore energyleadership by providing the owner or operator of a criticalenergy resource facility an interim permit under subtitle Cof the Solid Waste Disposal Act that is subject to finalapproval by the Administrator of the Environmental ProtectionAgency.[Page H855]&lt;/pre&gt;</constitutionalAuthorityStatementText>
